libdrawtext
------------------------------------------
libdrawtext is a simple library for fast anti-aliased text rendering in OpenGL.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.32-1
  libdrawtext0-0.2.1-1bl1
  libfreetype6-2.5.3-1
  libGL1-10.2.9-1
  libGLEW1.11-1.11.0-1
  libGLU1-9.0.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.24.51-6
  cygport-0.17.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-1
  libtool-2.4.2-5
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  http://nuclear.mutantstargoat.com/sw/libdrawtext/

Canonical download:
  http://nuclear.mutantstargoat.com/sw/libdrawtext/libdrawtext-0.2.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libdrawtext-0.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libdrawtext-0.2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libdrawtext-0.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdrawtext-0.2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdrawtext0-0.2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdrawtext-devel-0.2.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libdrawtext)
  /usr/bin/font2glyphmap.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libdrawtext.README
  /usr/share/doc/libdrawtext/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libdrawtext/COPYING.LESSER
  /usr/share/doc/libdrawtext/README

(libdrawtext0)
  /usr/bin/cygdrawtext-0.dll

(libdrawtext-devel)
  /usr/include/libdrawtext/drawtext.h
  /usr/lib/libdrawtext.dll.a

